    "course_title": "INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER VISION",
    "description": "Topics include image formation, feature detection, motion estimation, image mosaics, 3D shape reconstruction, and object recognition. Applications of these techniques include building 3D maps, creating virtual characters, organizing photo and video databases, human computer interaction, video surveillance, and automatic vehicle navigation. Broad overview of various computer vision and machine learning techniques and sensing and imaging technologies used in computer vision applications. This is a project-based course.",
